14 EMPLOYER-PROVIDED CHILD CARE CREDIT
15 SECTION 2.4.(a) Article 4 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes is amended by
16 adding a new Part to read:
17 "Part 6. Employer-Provided Child Care Credit.
18 "§ 105-163.20. Employer-provided child care credit.
19 (a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
20 (1) Code. – Defined in G.S. 105-228.90.
21 (2) Qualifying business. – A business subject to income tax under this Article.
22 (b) Credit. – A qualifying business that is allowed a credit against federal income tax for
23 qualified child care expenditures under section 45F of the Code shall be allowed as a credit
24 against the tax imposed by Part 1, Part 1A, or Part 2 of this Article, as appropriate, the amount
25 allowed under section 45F of the Code. In order to claim the credit allowed by this section, the
26 taxpayer must provide with the tax return the information required by the Secretary.
27 (c) Limitations. – A nonresident or part-year resident who claims the credit allowed by
28 this section shall reduce the amount of the credit by multiplying it by the fraction calculated under
29 G.S. 105-153.4(b) or (c), as appropriate. No credit shall be allowed under this section for amounts
30 deducted in calculating North Carolina taxable income. The credit allowed by this section may
31 not exceed the amount of tax imposed by Part 1, Part 1A, or Part 2 of this Article for the taxable
32 year reduced by the sum of all credits allowable, except for payments of tax made by or on behalf
33 of the taxpayer."
34 SECTION 2.4.(b) This section is effective for taxable years beginning on or after
35 January 1, 2026.
