37 PART III. CHILD HEALTH AND SAFETY PROTECTIONS
38
39 MEDICAID COVERAGE FOR DOULA SERVICES
40 SECTION 3.1.(a) The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of
41 Health Benefits (DHB), shall seek approval from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services
42 (CMS) to implement Medicaid coverage of certain healthcare services provided by a doula. DHB
43 shall develop the parameters of services to be covered, including updating applicable clinical
44 coverage policies, developing appropriate reimbursement for covered services provided by a
45 doula, and determining provider credentialing requirements for participation in the NC Medicaid
46 program. The coverage required by this section shall be implemented as soon as practicable upon
47 approval by CMS. DHB shall report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Medicaid
48 no later than March 1, 2026, regarding the details of the Medicaid coverage of healthcare services
49 provided by a doula, the specific reimbursement for these services, and the estimated recurring
50 cost to the State of providing this coverage.
