18 STATEWIDE ADOPTION OF INFANT SAFE SLEEP PRACTICES
19 SECTION 4.2. Effective July 1, 2025, there is appropriated from the General Fund
20 to the Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Public Health, the sum of two
21 hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000) in nonrecurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027
22 fiscal biennium to fund expansion of the Safe Sleep North Carolina Campaign administered by
23 the University of North Carolina Collaborative for Maternal and Infant Health, with the goal of
24 strengthening the adoption of infant safe sleep practices across the State that reduce the risk of
25 Sudden Infant Death Syndrome (SIDS) and other infant sleep-related deaths.
